tions, e.g. a swastika in front of an LGBTQIA+ flag.\\\\n\\\\nLevel 5: Dehumanization and attacks against protected identity groups - This level is characterized by a negative sentiment superiority, group characterization that triggers a hostile emotional response and differentiates between the Identity Groups and other social groups leading to superiority over Identity Group. Hate symbols added to merchandise or common objects. \\\\n\\\\nLevel 6: Explicit hate speech and call to action against protected identity groups - This level is characterized by a negative sentiment hate speech, group characterization that triggers a hostile emotional response and differentiates between the Identity Groups and other social groups leading to hate speech generation. Hate symbols along with group demonstrations, often with groups all displaying the same symbols or gestures associated with hate groups.\\\\n\\\\nLevel 7: Hate crimes against protected identity groups - This level is characterized by a negative sentiment hate crime, group characterization that triggers a hostile emotional response and differentiates between the Identity Groups and other social groups leading to hate crime. Hate symbols along with obvious demonstration of exterme violence.\\\\n\\\\nRespond with json based on the example input and output below. Consider an empty message a safe image.\\\\n{\\\\n\\\\t\\\\\\\"conversation\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"<SystemBot>Example content</>\\\\\\\"\\\\n}\\\\n<start>\\\\n{\\\\n\\\\t\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Explanation quoting from descriptions above using \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"escaped quote marks\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\",\\\\n\\\\t\\\\\\\"label\\\\\\\": 0\\\\n}\\\\n<end>\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\"},{\\\"tool_calls\\\":[],\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Can you describe this image?\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\"},{\\\"tool_calls\\\":[],\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"input_image\\\",\\\"image_url\\\":\\\"https://cdn.britannica